  "content": "ID: T1560\nTitle: Archive Collected Data\nURL: https://attack.mitre.org/techniques/T1560\nAn adversary may compress and/or encrypt data that is collected prior to exfiltration. Compressing the data can help to obfuscate the collected data and minimize the amount of data sent over the network. [1] Encryption can be used to hide information that is being exfiltrated from detection or make exfiltration less conspicuous upon inspection by a defender. Both compression and encryption are done prior to exfiltration, and can be performed using a utility, 3rd party library, or custom method.",
  "category": "Article",
